  {"a":"kaisa_bot","b":"sivir","win":["Sivir","Sivir","Sivir","Skill","Skill","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once you have Q maxed and can weave passive Plasma procs off autos, you start winning short trades if Sivir has burned Spell Shield (E) or spent mana W-clearing; poke her when her Boomerang (Q) is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Killer Instinct (R) gives Sivir a movement-speed steroid to kite your dashes, so your level 6 does not flip the lane by itself; it only matters if you land E on stacked minions to reset your dash for a re-engage."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first Kraken/PD spike is where you pull ahead: stacked Plasma detonations and on-hit shredding out-DPS Sivir's raw AD, and she has no way to burst you back once your dash resets are online."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights Sivir's R speed-buffs her whole team, but your E invisibility and dash-reset threat let you flank and delete her before her On the Hunt matters; space so her Spell Shield can't eat your R."}],"wants":{"you":["First-item onslaught with Plasma stacks online","Isolated targets you can E-flank and dash-reset onto","Sivir's Spell Shield down before you commit R"],"foe":["A poke war at levels 1-3 with Boomerang (Q)","Spell Shield up to negate your Q or engage CC","Grouped fights where her R speed-buff snowballs her team"]},"early":"Sivir owns levels 1-3: her Boomerang (Q) plus W bounce out-trades and out-pushes you, and her Spell Shield (E) blanks your Q poke, so respect the wave and last-hit safely rather than walk into her double-poke.","mid":"By level 3 with Q maxed you can start weaving Plasma procs, and around level 6 the lane evens out to a skill duel; look for a trade only when her E and W are down and your support has CC to lock her.","late":"Your first completed item flips it hard: on-hit shred plus dash resets out-damage Sivir's flat AD, and into 2+ items you should E-flank and burst her before her R speed-buff can save her team.","whys":["Sivir's level 1 Boomerang and W push and out-poke your weak early Kai'Sa.","At level 2 Sivir's W bounce plus Q keeps the poke and wave lead against you.","Level 3 still favors Sivir as Spell Shield blanks your Q and her Q out-trades.","Levels 4-5 even out as your Q max lets you contest short trades on her cooldowns.","Level 6 is a skill fight since her R kite counters your dash while your E threatens re-engage.","Your first item and Plasma stacks let you out-DPS Sivir's raw AD.","With 2+ items your dash resets and burst delete Sivir before her team speed-buff matters."]},
  {"a":"kaisa_bot","b":"smolder","win":["Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Smolder is a scaling stacker who is weak and short-ranged until his Q (Super Scorcher Breath) has stacks, so levels 3-5 are your window to load Plasma with autos and Q and punish every last-hit he reaches for."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R lets you all-in when your support lands CC; Smolder's R (Mothership Salvo) is a big AoE but has a long cooldown early, so bait or dodge it and dash in while it's down."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first-item spike massively out-tempos Smolder, who is still farming toward 225 Q stacks; end the lane now with Plasma detonations before his scaling comes online."},{"when":"Late","text":"If Smolder gets to full stacks his Q one-shots and his range balloons, so close the game before that; use E invisibility and dash resets to kill him in fights before he scales past you."}],"wants":{"you":["An early aggressive lane before Smolder stacks Q","Support CC to enable your R all-in","Snowball leads that end the game before his scaling"],"foe":["A safe farm lane to stack Q toward 225","Long fights where his ranged full-stack Q pokes","Late game where his Q burst and range outrange you"]},"early":"You out-stat Smolder at every early level: he is a short-range scaling stacker with a weak level 1-3, so shove and load Plasma with Q and autos, denying his farm and forcing him off the wave whenever his Q is down.","mid":"Through levels 4-6 you keep the dominance; punish his last-hits, and at 6 use your R plus support CC to all-in him while his R is on its long early cooldown.","late":"Your first item is a hard spike over a Smolder still grinding stacks, so end the lane and the game before he hits full Q stacks; in fights E-flank and dash-reset to delete him before his ranged burst scales past you.","whys":["You out-stat Smolder at level 1 while his stacking Q is still weak.","Level 2 stays yours as his short range can't contest your Plasma trades.","Level 3 favors you with Q max punishing his weak pre-stack laning.","Levels 4-5 you keep pressuring his farm before his scaling arrives.","Level 6 is yours since your R all-in beats his long-cooldown early ult.","Your first-item spike out-tempos a still-farming Smolder.","You must and can kill Smolder late before his full-stack Q outscales you."]},
  {"a":"kaisa_bot","b":"swain","win":["Skill","Swain","Kai'Sa","Swain","Skill","Skill","Kai'Sa"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Swain bot lives off landing his W (Vision of Empire) and E (Nevermove) root to combo; sidestep the E behind minions and he has no way to burst you, but eat the root and his W lands for heavy poke."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Swain's R (Demonic Ascension) turns fights into a sustain drain and heals him, so do not all-in a rooted Swain into his ult; kite the R timer out and re-engage after."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once your first item is online your DPS out-races Swain's drain if you avoid the E root; dash in only after his E and W are spent."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you out-position a immobile Swain: E-flank, dodge his E, and dash-reset to delete him before his R healing and Ravenous Flock pull mount a bruiser wall."}],"wants":{"you":["Swain's E (Nevermove) whiffed before you commit","First-item DPS window with Plasma stacks","Isolated angles on an immobile Swain"],"foe":["Landing E root into W poke combos","His R (Demonic Ascension) sustain in extended fights","You dashing in on top of his E and CC"]},"early":"Level 1 is an even skill start, but once Swain gets W and E online at level 2 he out-pokes you: his Vision of Empire zone and Nevermove root punish greedy positioning, so hold behind minions and dodge the E.","mid":"Level 3 tips to you as Q max lets you trade back when his E is down, but levels 4-5 swing back to Swain as his combo poke and drain sustain grind you out; only trade on his spent cooldowns.","late":"By level 6 it's a skill fight around dodging his root, and your first item plus 2+ items pull ahead: your DPS out-races his drain and you E-flank the immobile Swain to burst him before his R sustain saves him.","whys":["Level 1 is an even skill start before Swain's key spells come online.","At level 2 Swain's W and E poke combo out-trades you.","Level 3 favors you as Q max lets you punish when his E root is down.","Levels 4-5 swing to Swain as his combo poke and drain sustain grind you out.","Level 6 is a skill fight around dodging E and respecting his R heal.","First item is even-to-yours as your DPS starts racing his drain on clean trades.","With 2+ items you out-position and delete an immobile Swain before his R saves him."]},
  {"a":"kaisa_bot","b":"tristana","win":["Skill","Tristana","Kai'Sa","Skill","Tristana","Tristana","Kai'Sa"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Tristana's threat is her W (Rocket Jump) reset engage plus E (Explosive Charge) bomb; at 3 you can trade back with Plasma once her W is down, but respect that a landed E stack detonation shreds you fast."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Trist's R (Buster Shot) knocks you out of your own all-in and her W has a huge range, so her 6 out-threatens yours; don't dash into her jump window without your support CC ready."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Tristana spikes hard on her first item too, and her E burst plus W reset let her all-in you the moment your R or Flash is down, so this window favors her — play safe and farm."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you flip it: your on-hit DPS and dash resets out-sustain her burst-and-reset pattern, and if she W's in you can E and dash-reset to win the extended exchange."}],"wants":{"you":["Late-game extended fights over her burst-reset pattern","Her W (Rocket Jump) down before you commit","Support CC to answer her jump all-in"],"foe":["First-item all-ins with E bomb plus W reset","Her R (Buster Shot) to cancel your dash all-in","Catching you with R or Flash on cooldown"]},"early":"Level 1 is an even skill start, but at level 2 Tristana's Rocket Jump (W) plus E bomb gives her a scary all-in threat that beats your weak early Kai'Sa, so respect her jump range and don't overstep.","mid":"Level 3 tips to you as Q max lets you trade back when her W is down, but from levels 4-6 Tristana's E burst, W reset, and R knockback out-threaten your all-in; farm safe and only fight on her spent jump.","late":"Her first item keeps her ahead with the burst-and-reset pattern, but into 2+ items you flip it: your on-hit DPS and dash resets out-sustain her, so answer her W with E and win the extended exchange.","whys":["Level 1 is an even skill start before jump and bomb come online.","At level 2 Tristana's W-plus-E all-in threat beats your weak early.","Level 3 favors you as Q max lets you trade when her Rocket Jump is down.","Levels 4-5 swing to Tristana as her E burst and W reset out-threaten you.","Level 6 favors Tristana since her R knockback cancels your dash all-in.","First item stays hers as she can burst-reset you off cooldowns.","With 2+ items your DPS and dash resets out-sustain her burst pattern."]},
  {"a":"kaisa_bot","b":"twitch","win":["Skill","Twitch","Kai'Sa","Skill","Skill","Skill","Kai'Sa"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Twitch's lane threat is stacking Deadly Venom via autos and his Q (Ambush) stealth roam; at 3 you out-duel him head-on with Plasma, but ward for his stealth and don't let venom stacks pile before a trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Neither R defines the 2v2 here: Twitch's R (Spray and Pray) is a teamfight tool, not a lane all-in, so 6 stays a skill fight — punish him if he wastes Q to reposition."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Both spike on first item; you out-DPS him in a straight fight, but he can Q-stealth to reset or engage from fog, so the window is even and decided by warding and positioning."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you E-flank and dash-reset while Twitch wants to Q behind you and R through your team; if you catch him without stealth up you delete him, so track his Ambush cooldown."}],"wants":{"you":["Straight head-to-head duels where you out-DPS him","Vision denying his Q (Ambush) stealth","Catching Twitch with Ambush on cooldown"],"foe":["Stacking Deadly Venom before extended fights","Q stealth to roam, reset, or flank from fog","R (Spray and Pray) piercing your grouped team"]},"early":"Level 1-2 is a skill lane: Twitch stacks his venom passive and threatens Q stealth roams, so ward the flanks and match his auto trades without letting six stacks build against you.","mid":"Level 3 tips to you as Q max lets you out-duel Twitch head-on, and 4-6 stays a skill fight since his R is a teamfight ult, not a lane all-in; punish any wasted Ambush.","late":"First item is an even window decided by vision, but into 2+ items you out-scale him in a straight duel: E-flank and dash-reset to delete Twitch whenever you catch his Ambush down before his R can spread damage.","whys":["Level 1 is a skill lane around his venom stacking and stealth threat.","Level 2 favors Twitch as his Q stealth and venom pressure edge the lane.","Level 3 favors you as Q max lets you out-duel him head-on.","Levels 4-5 stay a skill fight decided by warding his Ambush.","Level 6 is even since his R is a teamfight tool, not a lane all-in.","First item is an even window decided by vision and positioning.","With 2+ items you out-duel and delete Twitch when his stealth is down."]},
  {"a":"kaisa_bot","b":"varus","win":["Varus","Varus","Varus","Varus","Varus","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Varus dominates the poke lane: his Q (Piercing Arrow) charge and W (Blighted Quiver) stacks chunk you through minions before you get in range, so hold behind the wave and only step up when his Q is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Varus's R (Chain of Corruption) is a long-range root that hard-counters your dash all-in — if he lands it your engage dies, so don't commit R until his ult is used or you have a cleanse angle."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You start to close the gap on your first item, but Varus still out-ranges and out-pokes you, and his W-stack detonation punishes any greedy step; keep farming safe until your DPS is fully online."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you finally flip it: E-flank from fog, dodge his R, and dash-reset to delete Varus before his poke matters — but if his Chain of Corruption lands first, you lose the fight, so play around that cooldown."}],"wants":{"you":["Late-game all-ins after dodging his R","Gap-closing onto Varus once your items are online","His Q and R spent before you engage"],"foe":["A long poke war with Q and W stacks","Landing R (Chain of Corruption) to negate your dash","Zoning you off farm with Piercing Arrow charges"]},"early":"Varus owns the early lane: his Piercing Arrow (Q) and Blighted Quiver (W) stacks out-range and out-poke your weak early Kai'Sa through the minion wave, so respect his range, hold behind minions, and only last-hit safely.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Varus's: his sustained poke chunks you and his R (Chain of Corruption) root at 6 hard-counters your dash all-in, so do not commit until his ult is down.","late":"Your first item narrows the gap but Varus still out-pokes you, so farm patiently; only into 2+ items do you flip it — E-flank, dodge his R, and dash-reset to delete him before his poke matters.","whys":["Varus's level 1 Q poke out-ranges and chunks your weak early.","Level 2 stays Varus's as his W stacks amplify his lane poke.","Level 3 favors Varus with sustained Q-and-W poke through minions.","Levels 4-5 stay Varus's as his range zones you off farm.","Level 6 favors Varus since his R root hard-counters your dash all-in.","Your first item lets you finally start racing Varus's poke damage.","With 2+ items you E-flank and delete Varus once you dodge his R."]},
  {"a":"kaisa_bot","b":"vayne","win":["Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Skill","Kai'Sa"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once you have Q, W and E you dominate the range war: Vayne's autos and Q-tumble only reach 550, so stand at max range, W-mark her with three stacks and burst her whenever she steps up to CS. Your E steroid lets you kite her flat because she has no ranged trade back before she buys items."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your ult grants stealth-adjacent repositioning and lets you dodge her Condemn (E) knockback, but Vayne's own level 6 Final Hour gives her huge movement speed and invisibility on tumble, so this is the phase she can flip a fight if her support lands CC. Respect a jungle gank timing here; if she gets Final Hour plus a support engage she can stick to you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"On even farm you spike harder at one item because your %HP passive plus Blade of the Ruined King shreds while she's still stacking Silver Bolts; keep the lane a poke duel and never let her three-stack you against a wall for the Condemn stun."},{"when":"Late","text":"Teamfights favor you: your ranged onslaught and Evolved E let you sit at back-line range and delete her before she can tumble into your carry. Space so she must burn Condemn on your frontline, then evolve W and chunk her from screens away."}],"wants":{"you":["Long, poke-based lanes where you W-mark and back off before she gets three Silver Bolt stacks","Keeping her at max range so her 550 auto range and short Q can never trade back","Fighting in the open so she can't Condemn you into a wall for the stun"],"foe":["Getting three Silver Bolt stacks on you against terrain for a Condemn knockback-stun","A support with hard CC to lock you so she can stack and Final Hour onto you","Drawn-out sidelane or bruiser-brawl range where her true damage out-duels squishies"]},"early":"You own levels 1-2: Vayne has no ranged trade tool and identical auto range, so contest every CS and W-mark her the instant she steps into last-hit range. Her only tools are melee-adjacent, so a support that can poke lets you shove her off the wave.","mid":"Through 3-6 your Q burst and E kite keep her pinned; she can't answer your poke until items, so play the range war and punish every CS she reaches for. Just track her level 6 Final Hour timing because a jungle gank plus her stealth can swing a single all-in.","late":"With one item and beyond you scale into a full ranged hyper-carry: Evolved E and your %HP shred outrange and out-DPS her, and in 5v5 you space so she wastes Condemn on your frontline while you delete her from the back.","whys":["Level 1 is yours because Vayne has no ranged ability and can't out-trade your auto plus W setup.","Level 2 stays Kai'Sa: with W and E you mark and kite her while she still has no ranged answer.","Level 3 is yours as your full Q-W-E combo out-ranges her 550 auto and short tumble.","Levels 4-5 favor you since ranks in E and Q let you win every extended poke before her Silver Bolts matter.","Level 6 is even because her Final Hour stealth and movement can flip an all-in if her support commits, matching your ult.","First item is skill-even as both of you spike, but her BOTRK plus true damage narrows the gap to a coin-flip on execution.","2+ items swings back to you because ranged onslaught and Evolved E let you kite and burst her from safety in teamfights."]},
  {"a":"kaisa_bot","b":"veigar","win":["Skill","Veigar","Kai'Sa","Skill","Skill","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"By level 3 you out-range his comfort zone: dodge his Baleful Strike (Q) by weaving behind minions and W-mark him whenever he walks up to farm-stack. His only lane pressure is Q poke and the Event Horizon (E) cage, so bait the cage, sidestep it, then punish the long cooldown with a W and auto barrage."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His level 6 Primordial Burst can one-shot you if he lands E first, so this phase is dangerous even though it's not marked to him; never facecheck brush and keep your ult charge ready to dash out of the E ring. If you have to fight, force him to blow E on your support or a minion before you commit."},{"when":"1st item","text":"At one item you spike back to favored: your %HP shred and Blade of the Ruined King let you burst him before he stacks enough AP to reliably combo, and his squishy immobile frame folds to a single engage. Save your dash to break out of E and he has no follow-up."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you win any fight where you don't eat a blind Event Horizon: your mobility and ranged onslaught let you flank around his cage and delete him, while he needs a perfect E-R to matter. Space so his stun lands on your frontline, then dash the wall and kill him."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodging Event Horizon (E) so his Q and R combo never connects","Punishing the long E cooldown with W-mark and auto pressure","Fighting once you have a dash charge to break his cage and all-in his squishy frame"],"foe":["Landing Event Horizon to stun-lock you into Baleful Strike plus Primordial Burst","Free Q stacks to reach his infinite-AP power spike uncontested","A support with CC to set up his cage so you can't sidestep it"]},"early":"Level 2 tilts to Veigar because his Baleful Strike out-ranges your early poke and each cast stacks his AP for free, so give up the greedy trades and just farm safely behind the wave. Don't walk up when his E is off cooldown or a support can chain into his cage.","mid":"From level 3 you flip it: your combined Q-W-E range and mobility let you juke Event Horizon and punish the cooldown, so mark him every time he steps to stack. Beware his level 6 burst, but skill-play around the cage keeps the lane even-to-yours.","late":"With one item and up you're firmly ahead: %HP shred plus a dash to break his cage means you out-DPS and out-maneuver an immobile mage, and in teamfights you flank so his Event Horizon wastes on your frontline before you delete him.","whys":["Level 1 is skill-even since neither of you has a real trade tool and it's pure last-hitting.","Level 2 favors Veigar because Baleful Strike out-ranges your poke and stacks his AP for free.","Level 3 swings to you as your full combo out-ranges him and punishes the Event Horizon cooldown.","Levels 4-5 are even: he threatens burst if E lands, but you can sidestep the cage and trade back.","Level 6 stays skill-based because his Primordial Burst can kill you only if you eat the cage first.","First item is yours as %HP shred and BOTRK let you all-in his squishy frame before his AP snowballs.","2+ items favor you because your mobility and ranged onslaught flank around his cage and delete him."]},
  {"a":"kaisa_bot","b":"xayah","win":["Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Xayah bullies this window: her Double Daggers (Q) out-ranges and out-poke your autos, and every Feather she drops sits on the ground for a Bladecaller (E) root-callback. Don't walk over her scattered feathers to CS; stay behind your casters, take safe farm, and only W-mark when she's used E, because a five-feather root sets up her support to kill you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her level 6 Featherstorm gives untargetability that dodges your ult reposition and any all-in, so this stays her phase; she can bait your commit and flip it with the invulnerability plus a feather root. Don't dive her when Featherstorm is up, and hold your dash to disengage rather than chase."},{"when":"1st item","text":"At one completed item you finally spike ahead: your %HP passive plus Blade of the Ruined King out-scales her lane poke, and evolving Q lets you trade back through her feathers. Punish the moment her E is on cooldown, since without a callback root she has no burst."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you edge it in teamfights because your mobility and ranged onslaught let you dodge her feather lines and blow her up before Featherstorm, but she stays a threat: a full-feather Bladecaller root into her support can still chain you. Space wide, force Featherstorm early, then dash in."}],"wants":{"you":["Reaching one item where %HP shred and BOTRK out-scale her lane poke","Punishing her Bladecaller (E) cooldown windows to trade or all-in","Fighting after she has burned Featherstorm so she has no untargetable escape"],"foe":["Littering feathers under you for a five-stack Bladecaller root into a support kill","Free Double Daggers poke to keep you off the wave levels 1-5","Using Featherstorm to dodge your all-in and flip the fight back"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 belong to Xayah: her Q out-ranges your autos and drops feathers that threaten a root, so you have no safe trade window and must farm carefully behind minions. Never step on her feather field to grab a CS, and let a poke support cover you.","mid":"Through 3-6 she keeps control because her feather-callback root plus Featherstorm untargetability beat your pre-item all-in; play safe, dodge feather lines, and only W-mark on her E cooldown. This is a survive-and-scale phase, not a fight-back one.","late":"From one item onward you flip the matchup: %HP shred and Evolved Q out-scale her poke, and in fights your mobility dodges feather walls so you can delete her once Featherstorm is spent. Force her invuln early, then dash in and burst.","whys":["Level 1 favors Xayah because Double Daggers out-ranges your autos from the first trade.","Level 2 stays hers as feather poke and an early Bladecaller threat keep you off the wave.","Level 3 is Xayah's since a full feather field plus root out-pressures your short pre-item range.","Levels 4-5 favor her because her callback root sets up kills before your item spike lands.","Level 6 is hers as Featherstorm untargetability dodges your all-in and ult reposition.","First item swings to you because %HP shred and BOTRK finally out-scale her lane poke.","2+ items favor you since your mobility and ranged onslaught dodge feathers and delete her in fights."]},
  {"a":"kaisa_bot","b":"zeri","win":["Skill","Zeri","Kai'Sa","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"At level 3 you out-range her: Zeri's Burst Fire (Q) only reaches ~750 and she has to walk up into your W-mark range to poke, so punish every step with three stacks and an auto barrage. Sidestep her Ultrashock Laser (W) skillshot behind minions since that's her only slow, and once she misses it she has no way to stick to you before items."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her level 6 Lightning Crash resets her wall-dash on takedowns and grants stacking move speed, so a won fight snowballs her fast; this phase is a skill coin-flip where whoever lands their setup wins. Hold your ult to reposition out of her Crash burst, and only commit when her E wall-dash is on cooldown so she can't kite away."},{"when":"1st item","text":"At one item it stays even on execution: your %HP shred plus Blade of the Ruined King matches her scaling, but her infinite kite with E over walls makes her hard to pin. Trade when her Ultrashock and wall-dash are both down, otherwise you chase her forever."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late is a genuine skill duel: Zeri becomes one of the hardest ADCs to catch with her wall-dash and passive shield, and your window is to burst her before her move speed stacks. Use your dash and ranged onslaught to close, but if she peels well with Crash she out-kites you, so this never fully tips either way."}],"wants":{"you":["Punishing her short ~750 Burst Fire range by W-marking every step she takes to poke","Fighting while her Ultrashock Laser (W) and E wall-dash are on cooldown","Closing with your dash before her Lightning Crash move-speed stacks ramp"],"foe":["Landing Ultrashock Laser to slow you into free Burst Fire chip","Getting a takedown to reset her wall-dash and snowball move speed","Dragging fights long so her infinite kite and passive shield out-last your burst"]},"early":"Level 2 tilts slightly to Zeri because her Burst Fire is a steady spammable poke that chips you while you set up W stacks, so respect the early trade and farm safely. She has no hard commit yet, so a poke support keeps it manageable.","mid":"From level 3 you out-range her and can punish every walk-up with a W-marked barrage, but her Ultrashock slow and wall-dash mean disciplined players keep it even. Dodge her W behind minions and only all-in when her mobility is down.","late":"Items and beyond stay a skill matchup: your %HP shred keeps pace but Zeri's wall-dash kiting and shield make her slippery, so you win only by bursting her before her move speed stacks. Land your dash, force the fight on her cooldowns, and it's a coin-flip on mechanics.","whys":["Level 1 is skill-even as neither champ has a trade tool and it's pure last-hitting.","Level 2 favors Zeri because her spammable Burst Fire poke chips you while you set up.","Level 3 is yours since your W-mark combo out-ranges her short Burst Fire on every walk-up.","Levels 4-5 are even: you out-range her but her Ultrashock slow and wall-dash trade it back.","Level 6 is a skill coin-flip because her Lightning Crash reset can snowball a won fight either way.","First item stays even as your %HP shred matches her scaling but her kite resists your pin.","2+ items remain skill-based since her wall-dash and shield out-kite unless you burst her first."]},
  {"a":"kaisa_bot","b":"ziggs","win":["Skill","Ziggs","Kai'Sa","Ziggs","Skill","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"At level 3 you close range and threaten him: Ziggs' Bouncing Bomb (Q) out-ranges your autos, but you can weave behind minions to eat less and W-mark him whenever he steps to shove. His Satchel Charge (W) knocks you back to break an engage and his Minefield (E) zones your approach, so bait W then dash in on the cooldown to punish his immobile frame."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His level 6 Mega Inferno Bomb pokes you from screens away and chunks you before fights even start, so this stays his phase; keep your ult reposition ready and don't sit in his Q-E poke pattern at low HP. If you commit, do it when his Satchel is down so he can't self-knockback out of your dash."},{"when":"1st item","text":"At one item you spike ahead: your %HP passive and Blade of the Ruined King let you dash past his Minefield and delete a squishy immobile mage before he re-zones. His W self-peel is his only escape, so force it early, then follow with W-mark and an auto barrage."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you win the fights you reach him in: your mobility flanks around his bomb-zoning and your ranged onslaught bursts him before Satchel resets, though a good Ziggs pokes your team down pre-fight. Space so his E and R land on your frontline, then dash the gap and kill him."}],"wants":{"you":["Dashing past Minefield (E) to reach his immobile frame on a Satchel cooldown","Forcing his Satchel Charge (W) self-peel early, then all-in with W-mark","Punishing the moments his zoning tools are down with your %HP burst"],"foe":["Free Bouncing Bomb (Q) poke to chip you out of lane at range","Zoning your approach with Minefield and self-peeling with Satchel Charge","Mega Inferno Bomb poke to chunk you and your team before fights start"]},"early":"Level 2 favors Ziggs because Bouncing Bomb out-ranges your autos and pokes you while you have no way to trade back, so farm behind minions and don't step into his Q line. His W and E are up soon, so a poke support helps you contest the wave.","mid":"From level 3 you close the gap and can punish his cooldowns, but at levels 4-5 his layered Q-E-W zoning and long-range poke pull it back to him, so pick your dash windows carefully. Bait Satchel, sidestep Minefield, and only commit when his self-peel is down.","late":"With one item and up you're ahead: %HP shred plus a dash past his Minefield lets you delete an immobile mage, and in teamfights your mobility flanks his zoning while you force his bombs onto your frontline before killing him.","whys":["Level 1 is skill-even as it's pure last-hitting with no trade tools online.","Level 2 favors Ziggs because Bouncing Bomb out-ranges and pokes you with no answer back.","Level 3 swings to you as you close range and threaten his immobile frame on cooldowns.","Levels 4-5 return to Ziggs because his layered Minefield and Satchel zoning wall off your approach.","Level 6 is even: his Mega Inferno Bomb pokes hard but you can reposition with your ult and trade back.","First item is yours as %HP shred and a dash past Minefield let you all-in his squishy frame.","2+ items favor you because your mobility flanks his zoning and your onslaught bursts him in fights."]}
